                <title>Favorite Cottage Recipes</title>
            </titleInfo>
            <abstract>
                <p>These recipes were on various pieces of paper overflowingly stored in a folder on
                    the inside of a kitchen cupboard door. The majority of the recipes are for high
                    carbohydrate foods, such as pancakes, waffles, cakes, and cookies, ideal for a
                    younger cottage population engaged outdoor activites on an unpredictable
                    schedule. The main course recipes appear intended to serve an unpredicably large
                    number of people, with an option for leftovers. Aside from Grandma Pier's
                    Applesauce Cake and one of the salads, the sources of the recipes are
                    unknown.</p>
            </abstract>
